      "content": "that \"misinterpretation\" thing sounds like a cover story to me. i was looking up how these IoT devices work and i saw that microphones and even thermal sensors are being used for way more than just \"comfort.\" if they can pick up on sound frequencies and humidity, couldn't they actually be analyzing my voice patterns or my breathing to figure out exactly what i'm feeling? like, is it even possible they're sending that data somewhere else to be processed?",
